The U command is used to disassemble one or several instructions.
Example:

\c -u
\c 305C:0000 8CD0              mov     ax, ss
\c 305C:0002 8CDA              mov     dx, ds
\c 305C:0004 29D0              sub     ax, dx
\c 305C:0006 31D2              xor     dx, dx
\c 305C:0008 B90400            mov     cx, 0004
\c 305C:000B D1E0              shl     ax, 1
\c 305C:000D D1D2              rcl     dx, 1
\c 305C:000F E2FA              loop    000B
\c 305C:0011 50                push    ax
\c 305C:0012 01E0              add     ax, sp
\c 305C:0014 83D200            adc     dx, +00
\c 305C:0017 83C00F            add     ax, +0F
\c 305C:001A 83D200            adc     dx, +00
\c 305C:001D 24F0              and     al, F0
\c 305C:001F 83FA01            cmp     dx, +01
